Barn: Ingvar f. 11, leg. läk., Barbro 17, sjuksköt. — Stud:-ex. i Gbg 02, teol. fil. ex. 04, teol. kand. i Lund 06, prakt. teol. prov o. prästv. 07. Kommin. i Eldsberga o. Tönner-sjö förs. 09, sjömanspräst i Stettin 12-19, kyrkoh. i Marstrand 19-27, i Stenkyrka sed. 27. Förordn. s. legations-pastor i Berlin o. sjömanspräst i London. Ordf. i Stenkyrka past :stämma, kyrkofullm. o. skolstyr.. Skärhamns kyrkofören., Klövedalskrets. av SvRK, led. av styr. f. BHlströmska folkhögsk. Skr.: art. i De våra i främmande land samt Julhälsningar t. förs. i Gbgs stift o. En julbok. LVO, Tyska RKGM.
translated: Cederberg, Teodor Gustav, church pastor, Sibräcka, born June 1, 1883 in Gothenburg to Teodor C. and Malin Dahlbom. Married in 1909 to Rut Gederberg. Children: Ingvar, born in 1911, a licensed physician, Barbro, born in 1917, a nurse. Teodor Gustav completed his high school studies in Gothenburg in 1902, theology and philosophy studies in 1904, theology studies in Lund in 1906, practical theology exam and ordained as a priest in 1907. He served as a parish assistant in Eldsberga and Tönnersjö from 1909, seaman's priest in Stettin from 1912-1919, church pastor in Marstrand from 1919-1927, and in Stenkyrka since 1927. He was appointed as a legation pastor in Berlin and seaman's priest in London. He was the chairman of Stenkyrka parish assembly, church council, and school board, as well as the Skärhamn church association and Klövedal district of the Swedish Red Cross. He was also a member of the board for the B. H. Lström Folk High School. He wrote articles for the "Our People Abroad" magazine and Christmas greetings for the congregations in Gothenburg Diocese and a Christmas book. He received the Royal Order of Vasa and the German Red Cross.
